For this task, I created a digital literacy awareness infographic using Canva. 
The aim of this infographic was to help students understand the importance of digital literacy in today’s world.
My design covered key topics such as the meaning of digital literacy, safe internet practices, and the importance of maintaining a professional online presence.
I used simple icons, short points, and a clean layout to make the content easy to understand and visually appealing.
The infographic highlights how students can use digital tools effectively while staying safe online.
I also included tips like using strong passwords, avoiding suspicious links, and being responsible on social media.
While creating the design, one challenge I faced was selecting the right amount of content without making the infographic look crowded. 
However, this helped me learn how to present information in a concise and effective way. 
Overall, this task improved my creativity and helped me understand how to communicate important digital concepts visually.
